Text: Mmmm...
*sigh*...
Alright, I'll ask you again.
...Eeep!!!
How did someone like you two...

....get special tickets only given to select
customers?!
I'll ask you one more time.
How did a couple of clowns like you two...
get your grubby hands on these tickets?!
W-W-W-W-We were g-g-given them!

You were "given them"? You didn't steal them or pick
them up somewhere?
Of course not! We just grabbed—er...were gifted them!
They were a gift from our friend Cid!
What?!
Yeah, it was Cid who told us to...
...invite the Mitsugoshi ladies on a date!!!
*gasp*!
Cid, as in Cid Kagenou?
Y-Yes!
My best buddy Cid Kagenou!
...Just as I expected.
By the way, do you happen to know Cid?
If you do, then how about we get to know each other—
Shut it.
Eek!!!
We shoulda never took those tickets—
Wasn't it your idea, Skel?

(To think he'd just give the tickets we prepared to
his classmates like this... Time to call the
others.)
Is Cid Kagenou coming on the date?
Of c-c-c-course.
H-He's coming, really! Cross my heart!

(I would never expect him to send a cryptic message
through his schoolmates—)
(What could Master Shadow possibly be up to?)
(I must consult with the Seven Shadows—)
So um...
H-How about that d-d-date?
It sounds like a wonderful idea.
Ohh!!!
I will kindly consider your offer, so—
Pipe down and wait here, you little brats!!!
Eeek!

Nu reports the matter to Alpha, and the Seven Shadows
convene for an emergency meeting.
I see...

He gave the tickets to his classmates and invited the
members of the Shadow Garden.

He seems to have some kind of motive behind inviting
us on a group date to Mitsugoshi Hot Spring Land.
By the way, what is "Mitsugoshi Hot Spring Land"?
Eta.
Ehh...um...
You designed it after all.

Mitsugoshi Hot Spring Land is a mega-resort
scheduled to open this week. It's based on the
legend of the "Dragon Tear"—
You're just reading what's written in the pamphlet.
"Dragon Tear"?
Master Shadow mentioned it that one time.
That one time...?
Playtime is over.
Gwah!
All clear here too.
That takes care of them.
I won't...give it to you...
the D...Dragon...Tear
I won't give you...that...
...golden...
Hmph!
Gah!
What's wrong, Shadow?

"Did something happen?"
"Did something—ah no, wait!"
...Are you familiar with the "Dragon Tear"?
...I've heard of it.
I believe it comes from a local legend.
Hmm...

An ancient legend. The salvation of souls. Excavate
the whole area.
But why?
Can't you see it?
The dazzling radiance filling this land.
The golden tears that drip from the heavens.
So...get digging.
Three days later, he left this place as if in a rush.

Surely he had an important mission only he could
handle.
He always does that—going off on his own.
But if that's his decision, we must accept it.

If he has unfinished business, we will complete it
for him.
But, what exactly is going on here—
Ah...
Something came out.
It's...
Yeah...a hot spring.
—That's how it all happened.
Yeah, now that you mention it.

Don't you think you're taking on too many side
projects?

In the end, all I could do was build the Hot Spring
Land, but...there's no way he just wanted to soak in
a hot spring.

Master Shadow was interested in the dragon legend
back then, but—
But, I don't sense any dragon magic...

Then the dragon may be a metaphor. Any links to the
Cult?

Cult activity in the area should have already been
wiped out.

...It's difficult to reach a conclusion with the
information we currently have.

It seems so... However, we will definitely figure it
out.
If we go on a hot spring date with him...
We gave him six tickets.
With his two school friends, that makes three guys...

It's only logical that three of us would accompany
them.
Three of us.
...Then the question is who goes.
I wanna go to the hot spring with Boss man.
Well, one of us was directly invited—

Just as Nu is speaking, a dagger made of slime comes
flying toward her.

Nu dodges it, but a second dagger flies to where she
lands.

You have other business to take care of, so you can't
go on this mission.
—Isn't that right?
No, I—
Isn't that right?
Yes, I'm too busy.
How immature...

That's it. That's the Shadow wisdom called
"power harassment."

This mission will be impossible to accomplish unless
it's one of the Seven Shadows.
*gasp*!
So I will—
Not so fast.

Shouldn't we choose based on who is best suited to
dealing with the outside world?
It should be someone with knowledge of the area.

The ability to manage the budget during the mission
is critical.

Considering the length of the mission, someone with
superior skills in magic would be appropriate.

Based on the volatility of the situation, wouldn't we
need someone who can act flexibly?
I'm gonna get in the hot spring with Boss man.
Looks like we're going to have to do it.
Nothing else needs to be said.
No need to make exceptions either.
There are three tickets.
So three winners.
I'm gonna go in the hot spring with Boss man.
Here we go.
Seven Shadows rock, paper, scissors!
Rock! Paper!
Scissors!
Shoot!!!
